ion: energy deposits are first summed\nper scintillator bar, and then converted to number of photoelectrons with a\ndata-driven procedure. This is followed by the same clustering algorithm and\nsame tracking code as in real data. We also report on the study of muon\ntransport through rock using PUMAS and GEANT4. In this paper we elaborate on\nthe rationale for our technical choices, including trade-off between speed and\naccuracy. The developments reported here are of general interest in muon\nradiography and can be applied in similar cases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Sep 2021 10:21:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 30 Sep 2021 08:31:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 17 Nov 2021 17:02:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-19"}
